														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1463969">
									

<p>Again, why? Let me put it this way: say you're the monster and twinkies are people (it's just an example, I am not making a fat joke), you're out having a good time swimming at the local YMCA; you're getting hungry though and a twinkie would be just perfect, now you can either use your magic teleportation powers to make a twinkie appear on the bench nearby or you can flop out of the pool and squirm around on the concrete in the parking lot looking for a dropped twinkie.</p>
<p>There really is no imperative for the thing to go to its prey when it can just wait for them to go in water before attacking them comfortably in an environment it's used to.</p>

