														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1463983">
									

<p>I didn't say it flopped around helplessly, the &quot;possibly less dangerous&quot; thing was a relative measure. It's basically the same thing with crocodiles: they're pretty dangerous on both land and in water, but they're more dangerous in water than they are on land.<br />
Plus, it can only teleport prey that know about it and immerse themselves in water, so it gets a free meal once that happens, but if only the former happens and the prey avoids water it might get impatient and take matters into its own hands, especially if the prey had escaped from it in the past.</p>

