								<div class="title" id="post-title-3882486">
																		Hypothetical containment measure
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/professor-wren" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4320988); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4320988&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252642" alt="Professor Wren" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4320988)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/professor-wren" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4320988); return false;" >Professor Wren</a></span> <span class="odate time_1532336745 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Jul 2018 09:05</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3882486">
									

<p>For all its ungodly ferociousness, 1128 is dependent on other entities being aware of its nature to pull them to its feeding ground. If you don't know what it looks like, it cannot bring you to it.</p>
<p>What would happen if 1128 <em>itself</em> didn't know this? Amnestics work to remove its ability to affect other living things, but what if those same amnestics were administered to 1128 itself? If it lost its knowledge of itself, would it be unable to pull things into its hunting grounds?</p>
<p>Food for thought.</p>

							</div>

								
					
